I have an expert grill 22 inch kettle style grill. Normal price is around $100 at Walmart, but some have them down around $70 on clearance. Decent grill, has and ash catcher, charcoal trays, and the lid has a thermometer to keep track of the heat. Been using it the past couple months and have had no problems with it. Only thing to note is the bottom grill for the coal seems to have warped a bit after having some high heat from fire starter cubes and a chimney for 20-30 minutes. No melting though and it still functions perfectly. If you aren’t a stickler for brands, it’s not a bad starter grill.
